   <title type="text">Poetic language in the epistles of Paulus Ritter Vitezović (1652-1713)</title>
   <content type="html"><![CDATA[<a href="https://osf.io/ek6pt/"><span style="font-size: small;"><span style="font-weight: normal;"><span class="overflow" id="nodeTitleEditable">Poetic language in the epistles of Paulus Ritter Vitezović (1652-1713)</span></span></span></a><br /><blockquote class="tr_bq"><span style="font-size: x-small;"><span style="font-weight: normal;"><span class="overflow" id="nodeTitleEditable"><span class="node-description overflow" data-type="textarea" id="nodeDescriptionEditable">An exploration of Latin usage in poetry of Croatian author Paulus Ritter Vitezović, including a comparison of his verse-endings with those of Ovid.</span></span></span></span><br /><h1><span style="font-size: x-small;">About Ritter's poetic language</span></h1><span style="font-size: x-small;">The hypothesis is that relatively little of poetic language characteristic for Ovid's epistles (<a href="https://github.com/PerseusDL/canonical-latinLit/raw/master/data/phi0959/phi002/phi0959.phi002.perseus-lat2.xml">Heroides</a>, <a href="https://github.com/PerseusDL/canonical-latinLit/raw/master/data/phi0959/phi008/phi0959.phi008.perseus-lat2.xml">Tristia</a>, <a href="https://github.com/PerseusDL/canonical-latinLit/raw/master/data/phi0959/phi009/phi0959.phi009.perseus-lat2.xml">Ex Ponto</a>) is present in the Neo-Latin epistles by Ritter Vitezović.</span><br /> <span style="font-size: x-small;">The hypothesis will be tested by examination of verse <strong>clausulae</strong> (verse endings): one, two, or three words at the end of verse. We want to see <em>how many clausulae from Ovid's epistles appear in Ritter Vitezović's texts</em>.</span><br /><br /> <span style="font-size: x-small;">Additionally, we will use the same procedure to compare <strong>beginnings</strong> of Ovid's and Ritter Vitezović's verses.</span></blockquote><span style="font-size: small;"><span style="font-weight: normal;"><span class="overflow" id="nodeTitleEditable"><span class="node-description overflow" data-type="textarea" id="nodeDescriptionEditable">&nbsp;</span>&nbsp;</span></span></span>                             ]]></content>
